      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FOREGONE CONCLUSION NZ (6) is in a purple patch of form having won his last two outings in this class, digging deep to get home by a half head at Shepparton last week. Draws wider but is going well enough to overcome that and land the hat trick. IMALLATTITUDE (2) draws much better than when far from disgraced last start. Worked but proved too good at Maryborough prior. Should get every chance from this barrier. ROCKLEIGHS LEGACY (7) was first up for two months when beaten 2.4m as runner-up at Kilmore last week. Draws wide but is open to improvement with that hitout under the belt. FREAK OUT (8) added to a string of wins and placings when scoring by a half neck at Melton last Friday. Draws on the back row this time so may need a touch of luck but the consistency is hard to knock. QUICK CRUNCH (10) is another starting from the second line but she is racing well with back-to-back wins last month, one here and the other from this row at Cranbourne.",
